A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Criminal Law – Theft – Redeemable Credit Points
3 FOR the purpose of prohibiting a person from knowingly or willfully obtaining or exerting
4 unauthorized control over certain points with the intent to deprive a certain owner
5 of the points; and generally relating to theft.
6 BY adding to
7 Article – Criminal Law
8 Section 7–111
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Criminal Law
14 7–111.
15 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
16 INDICATED.
17 (2) “OWNER” MEANS A PERSON WHO HAS A LAWFUL INTEREST IN OR
18 IS IN LAWFUL POSSESSION OF POINTS.
19 (3) (I) “POINTS” MEANS A TYPE OF CURRENCY EARNED BY A
20 CUSTOMER OF A BUSINESS BY COMPLETING REQUIREMENTS SET BY THE BUSINESS
21 THAT THE CUSTOMER MAY REDEEM FOR BENEFITS, GOODS, OR SERVICES.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb1319*

2 HOUSE BILL 1319
1 (II) “POINTS” INCLUDES:
2 1. RETAIL CREDIT;
3 2. CREDIT CARD POINTS;
4 3. TRAVEL POINTS; AND
5 4. FREQUENT FLYER MILES.
6 (B) A PERSON MAY NOT KNOWINGLY OR WILLFULLY OBTAIN OR EXERT
7 UNAUTHORIZED CONTROL OVER POINTS WITH THE INTENT TO DEPRIVE THE OWNER
8 OF THE POINTS.
9 (C) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES THIS SECTION IS GUILTY OF A FELONY AND
10 ON CONVICTION:
11 (1) IS SUBJECT TO IMPRISONMENT NOT EXCEEDING 5 YEARS OR A
12 FINE NOT EXCEEDING $10,000 OR BOTH; AND
13 (2) SHALL PAY THE OWNER THE VALUE OF THE POINTS.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
15 October 1, 2025.

